## Before all
I highly recommand to do it with short videos to avoid some crash (browser, stylus, etc), this because of the code you'll need copy/paste at the end of this tutorial. Works very well with videos generated by Kindroid from a selfie.
## Download the video
Download the video you want use as avatar or background from your video gallery in selfie page.
## Convert video
Unfortunately Stylus don't accept videos so we need convert the video in an image format who accept animations.
For this example i'll take a video file like:
- lenth: 6 seconds
- weight: 475ko
- resolution: 720x720
For this we have some choices:
- APNG: good colors, animations are better than with GIF but file weight is bigger (almost 280mo)
- GIF: bad colors, not fluid animations, big file weight (28.2mo)
- AVIF/AVIFS: good colors, perfect animations, good file weight (280ko) (AVIF is for static images, AVIFS for animated images)
So you understand easily i think, we'll use AVIF/AVIFS format.
Go here https://ezgif.com/video-to-avif, upload the video and click on Convert to AVIF! blue button.
Scroll down and right click on the animated image under Output AVIF animation: then Save image to
## How to avoid host the AVIFS file
Ezgif website is good but he don't keep converted file more than 1 hour so you can't use a link to his server and except if you have your own server can be difficult to find where to host the file, mostly because AVIF/AVIFS format is new so not supported by many platforms and if it's a NSFW file you can't host it on many platform too.
Here a solution, go to https://ezgif.com/image-to-datauri (yes again this website), upload your AVIFS file, in Include tags for: choose Nothing then click on Convert to data URI! blue button.
You'll get a thing like this (don't be affraid ðŸ˜‚ and scroll down to read the end of the guide):

Enable avatar choice or background then paste the weird code between quotes.
